<p>next morning he blew the QM. up properly &amp; it done him the world of good, we laid here for 2 day's waiting for the rough gales to ease up a bit for it would be almost impossible to land us with such a heavy sea running.<br/>When we left Lemnos we did not know properly whether we were going to Anzac or Salonika, but once we started we were not left long in doubt. I forgot to mention that as we were marching down to the pier, a lot of nurse's came out &amp; presented us with a fine Australian flag &amp; we still have it (25/4/16) There were a few Canadian hospitals</p>
